<div class="bibEntry"><p class="bib special">202. Maiotti, Ettore. The Watercolor Handbook: Learning from theMasters. New York: Clarkson N. Potter, 1986. 159 pp. Index, glossary, B/W illus., color illus. ISBN 0-517-56306-1. </p><p class="annot">A practical guide to watercolor painting, this book teaches techniqueby example. The author asserts that color and value are as integral to successful watercolor technique as water. The emphasis on color mixing, value distribution in compositions, and careful analysis of master works makes this a fine guide for the student interested in water media. Lessons are concise and lucid and the writing style is very readable. The authorâ€™s approach to watercolor is fresh and inspiring. </p></div>
